{"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For security reasons, chat history by default has a temporary nature and gets killed when providing another credentials into "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/Jivo","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"code":"Jivo\/session","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/JVSessionController\/setup(widgetID:clientIdentity:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", or by calling "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/Jivo","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Jivo\/session"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/JVSessionController\/shutDown()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"It means, for example, if your client logs-out and then logs-in again, you may see him as entirely new client.","type":"text"},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Even in case he uses the same login credentials, and even in case you provide the same user_token for him into SDK."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To keep chat history alive between login sessions, you have to generate JWT token and use it as user_token."},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"text":"Below, we explain how to do that.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"1-Prepare-secret","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"#1: Prepare secret"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"First, you need to create your global "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"secret"},{"type":"text","text":" which you’ll use for generating JWT tokens."},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"text":"Please create it accordingly to RFC 7519, with length of 256 bit.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Then, place this secret into “JWT Settings” screen of your Mobile SDK channel options."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You may found this resource useful to generate, sign, and check JWT tokens: ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/jwt.io\/","isActive":true}]}],"name":"Tip","style":"tip"},{"anchor":"2-Generate-token","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"#2: Generate token"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"JWT tokens you will generate for your clients, must:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"contain unique “id” field for each individual client","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"be encrypted using your ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"secret"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Minimal JWT payload must contain “id” field which acts like a client identifier, so here is example of such JWT payload:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["{","    \"id\": \"egor531@example.com\"","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Finally, you should feed your JWT as userToken parameter into:","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/Jivo","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Jivo\/session"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/JVSessionController\/setup(widgetID:clientIdentity:)"}]},{"name":"Important","type":"aside","style":"important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For security reasons, you’d better generate 